examples.content:
Chop 1 green chilli. Chop 1/2 medium onion. Chop 1 medium tomato. Chop 3 tbsp coriander leaves. Cut two slices of bread into bite-size pieces. Heat a pan with 1 tbsp oil. Add 1/2 tsp jeera and wait till it sizzles. Add chopped chillies and Onions and Wait until the onion turns golden. Add 1 teaspoon of ginger garlic paste. Saute until the raw smell goes off. Add chopped tomatoes. Add 1 tsp salt, 3/4 tsp chilli powder, and 1/2 tsp garam masala. Mix all ingredients and cook until the masala leaves the pan. Pour 3 tbsp of water and cook further until water evaporates. Transfer the bread slices and turn off the stove. Gently mix the bread and mixture. Avoid overmixing as the bread gets mushy. Sprinkle 3 tbsp chopped coriander leaves.
